TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
The solution of the equation
\[\sqrt{2x-1} -5 = 0 \]
is \(x=\)  \{ ans_rule(4) \}.
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(13));





TEXT(EV3(<<'EOT'));
$BR Hint:  This is much like the preceding problem.
EOT

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'EOT'));
$BR $BBOLD Solution:$EBOLD
Again we isolate the square root and square:
\[
\begin{array}{rclcl}
\sqrt{2x-1} - 5 &=& 0 &|& +5 \\
\sqrt{2x-1} &=& 5 &|& ()^2\\
2x-1 &=& 25 &|& + 1 \\
2x &=& 26 &|& \div 2 \\
x &=& 13 &|& \hbox{the answer} \\
\end{array}
\]

EOT






